      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: support baseURL alias in memory embedding provider config resolution",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen users configure `models.providers.openai.baseURL` (camelCase with capital R) pointing to a local Ollama or OpenAI-compatible endpoint, `ModelProviderSchema` silently drops the `baseURL` key via `.strict()`. Memory embeddings then fall through to the built-in OpenAI adapter and route to `api.openai.com/v1` instead of the configured local endpoint.\n\nFixes #93396\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/config/zod-schema.core.ts:495-522` | Accept `baseURL` as optional field + normalize to `baseUrl` in `superRefine`. Downstream code only reads `baseUrl` — no changes needed. URL redaction is auto-fixed (covers `baseUrl` paths). |\n| `src/agents/memory-search.ts:182-185` | Skip built-in adapter when provider has custom `baseUrl`. Before: a `providerId === \"openai\"` match returned the direct adapter unconditionally. After: checks `providerConfig.baseUrl` and skips when configured. |\n| `src/config/schema.test.ts` | +2 tests: normalization of `baseURL` → `baseUrl`, and `baseUrl` priority over `baseURL` |\n| `src/agents/memory-search.test.ts` | +2 tests: skip adapter with custom baseUrl, use adapter without one |\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Fix for issue #93396 — `models.providers.*.baseURL` is accepted by `.strict()` and normalized to canonical `baseUrl`, routing memory embeddings to the configured endpoint instead of `api.openai.com/v1`.\n\n**Real setup tested**: Node.js v24.13.1 on Linux x86_64\n\n**Exact steps or command run after fix**:\n```bash\n# 1. Schema normalization — real production code path\nnode --import tsx /tmp/verify-baseurl-normalize.mjs\n\n# 2. Tests\ncd $WORKTREE\npnpm test src/agents/memory-search.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n```\n$ node --import tsx /tmp/verify-baseurl-normalize.mjs\n\n=== Test 1: baseURL → baseUrl normalization ===\nInput:  { baseURL: 'http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1' }\nOutput: baseUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1\"\nPASS: true\n\n=== Test 2: baseUrl already set → baseURL ignored ===\nInput:  baseUrl='https://my-proxy.example.com/v1', baseURL='http://ignore-me.local:11434/v1'\nOutput: baseUrl = \"https://my-proxy.example.com/v1\"\nPASS: true\n\n=== Test 3: Memory search routing ===\nProvider 'openai' with custom baseURL:\n  embedding provider: skipped (custom endpoint)\nPASS: true (built-in adapter skipped)\n\n✅ All 3 real-behavior checks pass\n\n$ pnpm test src/agents/memory-search.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts\n ✓ |unit-fast| src/agents/memory-search.test.ts (37 tests)\n ✓ |runtime-config| src/config/schema.test.ts (57 tests)\n\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  94 passed (94)\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: `baseURL` passes `.strict()` validation. The existing `superRefine` normalizes it to `baseUrl` in-place, so all downstream call sites (memory search, provider config, embedding client, remote client, gateway `/v1/embeddings`) work without changes — they already read `baseUrl`. URL redaction also works because `baseUrl` is already in the sensitive URL path list.\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end with a running Ollama instance serving embeddings. Schema normalization and routing logic are independently verified.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n```bash\npnpm test src/agents/memory-search.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts\n# Test Files  2 passed (2)\n#      Tests  94 passed (94)\n```\n\n*AI-assisted: built with Claude Code*",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93396-Bug----Provider-name--openai",
